<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,834,1699,1724]" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
Notes on 
<taxonomicName authority="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityName="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityYear="1955" box="[261,834,1699,1724]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucranioides">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[261,564,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Dichotomius eucranioides</emphasis>
Pereira &amp; D’Andretta
</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="416" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1772,2012]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,284]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="416" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">
Since the time of its description (
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V." box="[525,838,1772,1796]" journalOrPublisher="Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" pagination="247 - 264" part="12" refId="ref8144" refString="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V. (1955) Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae). Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 12, 247 - 264." title="Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae)" type="journal article" year="1955">Pereira &amp; D’Andretta 1955</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityYear="1955" box="[859,1039,1772,1796]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucranioides">
<emphasis box="[859,1039,1772,1796]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">D. eucranioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has maintained a doubtful position within the subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[386,571,1808,1832]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Luederwaldtinia">
<emphasis box="[386,571,1808,1832]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Luederwaldtinia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V." box="[587,916,1807,1831]" journalOrPublisher="Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" pagination="247 - 264" part="12" refId="ref8144" refString="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V. (1955) Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae). Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 12, 247 - 264." title="Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae)" type="journal article" year="1955">Pereira &amp; D’Andretta (1955)</bibRefCitation>
did not assign this species to a species group but Vulcano 
<emphasis box="[295,353,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">et al.</emphasis>
(1967) later placed it in the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Eschscholtz" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[676,786,1844,1868]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assifer">
<emphasis box="[676,696,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[711,786,1844,1868]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">assifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group due the presence of a transversal carina on the head of males. However, we believe that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityYear="1955" box="[662,842,1880,1904]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="415" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucranioides">
<emphasis box="[662,842,1880,1904]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">D. eucranioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
should be considered to be in its own species group within the subgenus for the following reasons: it is the only species in the genus that has a crenulate clypeal margin (
<figureCitation box="[159,227,1952,1976]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1417,1440]" captionTargetBox="[185,1391,209,1379]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[167,1403,195,1387]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dichotomius eucranioides (A) black arrow indicating crenulated clypeal margin; D. sexdentatus (B) black arrow indicating tooth or protuberance on clypeogenal junction (this is also seen on D. eucranioides); D. nisus (C) black arrow indicating the asymmetry of the parameres; D. crinicollis (D) black arrows indicating pilosity on the hypomeron; D. superbus (E) white arrow indicating gibbosities on the pronotum; D. schiffleri (D. sericeus species group) (F) white arrow indicating a fovea on the posterior angle of the pronotum; D. speciosus (G) black arrows indicating cephalic transversal carina; D. agenor (H) black arrow indicating male cephalic carina; D. glaucus (D. carbornarius species group) (I) elytra microsculpture." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/224053/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="415">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A); the transversal carina width on the head is subequal to the distance between the eyes and is greater than its height; the pronotal disc of males is anteriorly delimited by four gibbosities; the pronotal declivity of males has two lateral depressions filled with ocellate punctures; and, contrary to the species of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Eschscholtz" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1119,1230,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="assifer">
<emphasis box="[1119,1139,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1155,1230,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">assifer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species group, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityYear="1955" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucranioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. eucranioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
hypomeron do not have an anterior excavation delimited medially by a dense brush of red setae. Although 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Pereira &amp; D'Andretta" authorityYear="1955" box="[264,443,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Dichotomius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eucranioides">
<emphasis box="[264,443,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">D. eucranioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a brachypterous species, we decided not to redescribe herein since the descriptions of the female (
<typeStatus box="[283,385,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">holotype</typeStatus>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V." box="[396,703,260,284]" journalOrPublisher="Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" pagination="247 - 264" part="12" refId="ref8144" refString="Pereira, F. S. &amp; D'Andretta, M. A. V. (1955) Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae). Papeis Avulsos do Departamento de Zoologia, 12, 247 - 264." title="Novos escarabeideos e novas sinonimias (Col. Scarabaeidae)" type="journal article" year="1955">Pereira &amp; D’Andretta 1955</bibRefCitation>
) and of the male (
<bibRefCitation author="Vulcano, M. A. &amp; Pereira, F. S. &amp; Martinez, A." box="[906,1128,260,284]" journalOrPublisher="Studia Entomologica" pageId="5" pageNumber="416" pagination="515 - 530" part="19" refId="ref8469" refString="Vulcano, M. A., Pereira, F. S. &amp; Martinez, A. (1976) Notas sobre Scarabaeoidea Americana (Col. Lamellicornia). Studia Entomologica, 19, 515 - 530." title="Notas sobre Scarabaeoidea Americana (Col. Lamellicornia)" type="journal article" year="1976">
Vulcano 
<emphasis box="[1008,1065,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="416">et al.</emphasis>
1976
</bibRefCitation>
) are detailed enough.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
